track_notes: Going up is a lot of fun, going down is much longer and some sections of the trail are quite exhausting. (The park authorities want you to use a different trail for the descent so as not to endanger ascending people with falling rocks.) It took us over 7 hours (3:20h up, 4:10h down) for the round trip (not including the time we spent on the summit). A young couple we spoke to did the round trip in 4:30h.
